      • onStartLoading

        protected void onStartLoading()
        Starts an asynchronous load of the Loader's data. When the result is ready the callbacks will be called on the process's main thread. If a previous load has been completed and is still valid the result may be passed to the callbacks immediately. The loader will monitor the source of the data set and may deliver future callbacks if the source changes.

        Must be called from the process's main thread.

        Overrides:
        onStartLoading in class android.support.v4.content.Loader<Boolean>
